        "# Orchestration\n",
        "\n",
        "Coordinating multiple agents into workflows.\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "## Why orchestrate?\n",
        "\n",
        "A single agent is powerful. Real-world problems need several specialized agents working together — like a delivery operation where one person receives orders, another packages, another ships.\n",
        "\n",
        "**Benefits:**\n",
        "\n",
        "- **Separation of concerns** — debug one step, not the whole system\n",
        "- **Reliability** — retry failed steps independently\n",
        "- **Flexibility** — branch, loop, parallelize\n",
        "- **Reusability** — a \"send email\" task works for orders, resets, and alerts\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "## Orchestration patterns\n",
        "\n",
        "**Sequential** — A, then B, then C:\n",
        "\n",
        "```\n",
        "Receive Order → Validate Payment → Prepare Package → Ship\n",
        "```\n",
        "\n",
        "**Conditional** — branch based on conditions:\n",
        "\n",
        "```\n",
        "Check Type → Standard Shipping / Express Shipping\n",
        "```\n",
        "\n",
        "**Map-Reduce** — process in parallel, combine:\n",
        "\n",
        "```\n",
        "Input List → [Process A] [Process B] [Process C] → Combine\n",
        "```\n",
        "\n",
        "**Loop** — repeat until a condition is met:\n",
        "\n",
        "```\n",
        "Process Item → Done? → No → Process Item → Done? → Yes\n",
        "```\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "# The landscape\n",
        "\n",
        "Pre-built agents vs. building your own.\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "## Pre-built agents {.smaller}\n",
        "\n",
        "**Personal AI assistants** (live in messaging apps):\n",
        "\n",
        "- **OpenClaw** — massive Node.js agent, huge plugin ecosystem, needs strict sandboxing\n",
        "- **Nanobot** — lightweight Python alternative, minimal RAM, deploys on cheap servers\n",
        "\n",
        "**Coding agents** (live in your terminal/IDE):\n",
        "\n",
        "- **OpenCode** — Go-based, modern TUI, desktop app, LSP integration, 75+ LLM providers\n",
        "- **Aider** — Python-based, terminal-only, Git-native workflow, every change is a clean commit\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "## CodeTrain — build your own agent\n",
        "\n",
        "A minimalist orchestration engine inspired by PocketFlow. Instead of buying a \"finished car,\" you build custom agents from an \"engine block.\"\n",
        "\n",
        "**Why CodeTrain?**\n",
        "\n",
        "- Total ownership — you understand every line of routing logic\n",
        "- Self-looping agents — chatbots that loop back to themselves\n",
        "- SKILL.md integration — feed the architecture to OpenCode and it builds for you\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "## The CodeTrain architecture {.smaller}\n",
        "\n",
        "Three concepts:\n",
        "\n",
        "| Concept | Role | Analogy |\n",
        "|---|---|---|\n",
        "| **Manifest** | Shared dictionary flowing through the system | The cargo |\n",
        "| **Jobs** | Units of work with 3 stages | Workstations |\n",
        "| **Hustle** | The route connecting jobs | The delivery route |\n",
        "\n",
        "Every Job has three stages:\n",
        "\n",
        "1. `receive_order()` — load input from manifest\n",
        "2. `prepare_order()` — do the work (call LLM, process data)\n",
        "3. `ship_order()` — store results back in manifest\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "## Your first Job\n",
        "\n",
        "```python\n",
        "import codetrain as ct\n",
        "\n",
        "class GreetingJob(ct.Job):\n",
        "    def receive_order(self, manifest):\n",
        "        return manifest.get(\"name\", \"World\")\n",
        "\n",
        "    def prepare_order(self, name):\n",
        "        return f\"Hello, {name}!\"\n",
        "\n",
        "    def ship_order(self, manifest, name, greeting):\n",
        "        manifest[\"greeting\"] = greeting\n",
        "        return \"done\"\n",
        "\n",
        "job = GreetingJob()\n",
        "manifest = {\"name\": \"Ghana\"}\n",
        "job.run(manifest)\n",
        "print(manifest[\"greeting\"])  # Hello, Ghana!\n",
        "```\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "## Chaining Jobs\n",
        "\n",
        "Connect Jobs with the `>>` operator for sequences and `- \"action\" >>` for conditional branches.\n",
        "\n",
        "```python\n",
        "# Sequential: extract → format → respond\n",
        "workflow = ExtractNameJob() >> FormatJob() >> RespondJob()\n",
        "workflow.run(manifest)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Conditional branching\n",
        "workflow = (\n",
        "    ClassifyJob()\n",
        "    - \"simple\" >> QuickReplyJob()\n",
        "    - \"complex\" >> DeepAnalysisJob()\n",
        ")\n",
        "```\n",
        "\n",
